fr.sii.ogham.sms.encoder

Class EncodedWithHeader

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sii.ogham.sms.encoder.EncodedWithHeader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Encoded

    public class EncodedWithHeader
extends Object
implements Encoded
    The encoded message into a byte array also contains a header.

    This happens for example when a message is split into several segments. The header is used to indicate how the message was split (see User Data Header).

    getBytes() returns the whole message (header + payload).

    • Constructor Detail

      • EncodedWithHeader

        public EncodedWithHeader(byte[] header,
                         Encoded payload)
        Initializes with the header byte array and the encoded message (byte array and charset unsed to encode it).

        The whole segment byte array is generated by creating a new array of bytes, appending header bytes and appending Encoded.getBytes().

        Parameters:
        header - the header bytes
        payload - the encoded message without the header.
